```

Note: Testing `__CLI_VERSION__` injection requires mocking the global, which is complex. The primary test cases cover the env override and package.json fallback paths which are most important for dev mode.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `SERVER_VERSION` resolves with priority: DORKOS_VERSION_OVERRIDE > __CLI_VERSION__ > package.json
- [ ] `IS_DEV_BUILD` is `true` when version matches `0.0.0` pattern AND no override/CLI version
- [ ] `IS_DEV_BUILD` is `false` when `DORKOS_VERSION_OVERRIDE` is set (even to `0.0.0`)
- [ ] `IS_DEV_BUILD` is `false` when `__CLI_VERSION__` is defined
- [ ] `DORKOS_VERSION` renamed to `DORKOS_VERSION_OVERRIDE` in env.ts and turbo.json
- [ ] Tests written and passing

Modify `apps/server/src/services/core/update-checker.ts` to skip the npm registry fetch entirely when running a dev build.

## Current State

The file at `apps/server/src/services/core/update-checker.ts` unconditionally fetches from npm:
```typescript
export async function getLatestVersion(): Promise<string | null> {
  if (Date.now() - lastChecked < CACHE_TTL) return cachedLatest;
  try {
    const controller = new AbortController();
    const timeout = setTimeout(() => controller.abort(), FETCH_TIMEOUT);
    const res = await fetch('https://registry.npmjs.org/dorkos/latest', {
      signal: controller.signal,
    });
    // ...
  } catch {
    return cachedLatest;
  }
}
```

## Implementation

Add the dev build guard at the top of `getLatestVersion()`:

```typescript
import { IS_DEV_BUILD } from '../../lib/version.js';

export async function getLatestVersion(): Promise<string | null> {
  // Skip npm registry fetch entirely in dev mode — no phoning home
  if (IS_DEV_BUILD) return null;

  if (Date.now() - lastChecked < CACHE_TTL) return cachedLatest;
  // ... rest unchanged
}
```

## Tests

Extend or create `apps/server/src/services/core/__tests__/update-checker.test.ts`:

```typescript
import { describe, it, expect, vi, beforeEach } from 'vitest';
import { getLatestVersion, resetCache } from '../update-checker.js';

// Mock the version module
vi.mock('../../../lib/version.js', () => ({
  IS_DEV_BUILD: false,
  SERVER_VERSION: '1.0.0',
}));

describe('getLatestVersion', () => {
  beforeEach(() => {
    resetCache();
    vi.restoreAllMocks();
  });

  it('returns null immediately when IS_DEV_BUILD is true', async () => {
    vi.mocked(await import('../../../lib/version.js')).IS_DEV_BUILD = true as any;
    const fetchSpy = vi.spyOn(globalThis, 'fetch');
    const result = await getLatestVersion();
    expect(result).toBeNull();
    expect(fetchSpy).not.toHaveBeenCalled();
  });

  it('fetches from npm registry in production mode', async () => {
    vi.mocked(await import('../../../lib/version.js')).IS_DEV_BUILD = false as any;
    vi.spyOn(globalThis, 'fetch').mockResolvedValue(
      new Response(JSON.stringify({ version: '1.2.0' }), { status: 200 })
    );
    const result = await getLatestVersion();
    expect(result).toBe('1.2.0');
  });
});
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `getLatestVersion()` returns `null` without any network request when `IS_DEV_BUILD` is `true`
- [ ] `getLatestVersion()` still fetches from npm when `IS_DEV_BUILD` is `false`
- [ ] No behavior change for production builds
- [ ] Tests written and passing

Extract `isNewer()` and `isFeatureUpdate()` from `VersionItem.tsx` into a shared utility file within the status feature module, and export from the barrel. This eliminates the duplicate `isNewer()` in `ServerTab.tsx`.

## Current Duplication

